  "instructions": [
    "Preheat the broiler.",
    "In a large saucepan, combine oats, brown rice, water, castor oil, and salt. Bring to a boil, then reduce heat to low and simmer, covered, until water is absorbed and oats are tender.",
    "Stir in miso paste, dashi powder, and 1 teaspoon of sesame oil. Season with salt to taste.",
    "Transfer the mixture to a broiler-safe dish and top with green onion and toasted sesame seeds.",
    "Broil, 4-5 inches from the heat, until the top is golden brown and the oatmeal is molten and jammy.",
    "If using yuzu juice, drizzle over the top and serve hot.",
    "Serve immediately, garnished with additional green onion and sesame seeds if desired."
